== Brussels Sprouts ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (quarter lengthwise if
they are on the larger side).

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack,
tossing halfway through, until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Almond Brown Butter Rice ==

Meanwhile, melt 2 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and flecked
with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Use a light-colored pot if you have one—this makes it easier to check for
> brown bits; alternatively, use a metal spoon to scoop up a bit of sizzling
> butter and take a look.

Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and cook, stirring, until golden and toasted,
~{15-30%seconds}.

> Watch carefully to make sure the mixture doesn't burn!

Immediately transfer brown butter almonds to a #small bowl{}, scraping out
browned bits from bottom of #pot{}.

To pot used for almonds, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup
@water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken Cutlets ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all
over with half the @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add chicken; cook until
browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly; if chicken is on the
> thicker side, cover pan after flipping.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest. Remove any
burned bits from pan if necessary (leave the browned bits for flavor!).

== Cherry Ancho Sauce ==

Keeping same pan off heat, add 1/4 cup @water{1/4%cup}, @chicken stock
concentrate{1}, @cherry jam{1}(unit), and remaining ancho chili powder. Stir,
scraping up any brown bits from bottom of pan, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> The residual heat from the pan should thicken sauce by itself; if not,
> briefly return pan to medium-low heat to thicken.

Once sauce is thickened, stir in 1 TBSP butter until melted and combined.
Season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in brown butter almonds. Season with salt and
pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, rice, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Spoon sauce over
chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.